caption: One of my families favorite spots in the neighborhood and is often our go too. Food is always fresh and delicious and that’s why we come here! It feels like home and it’s also the BEST value in Hayes Valley.

Utterly charming interior space, wonderful service, plentiful menu and fair prices. Don't miss out on the tiramisu dessert!!

The Best. Drop the mic. End of conversation. Neighborhood restaurant was here long before the gentrification of Hayes Valley and trendy container-shops came around. Perfection never disappoints. Try Takeout! It arrives great, always hot and fresh.
Great atmosphere! Delicious pasta 🍝. Always had a wonderful experience before I moved....

Lovely, no wait on a Sunday.

Good food but, the fact that I can customize my dish let's me know that the dishes aren't specialized. Also the fact that chicken parmigiana has mozzarella really irks me. But the pasta tasted like pasta which was nice. I ordered the pesto which I was craving and I was glad to have it that night.

This is one of the best restaurants in San Francisco. It's crazy it's not packed all the time. They make everything fresh. Come on guys eat here! Get the Tiramisu.

Family run, friendly, delicious meals, well priced and fantastic atmosphere.  Review update: changed from 5 to 3 stars due to the overall lack of consistency in the experience and food. Sometimes 5 stars, but sometimes much less.

Reasonable prices cozy atmosphere my pizza was clearly made fresh very thin crust and it looked like most food was made fresh.

Intimate, red-checkered-table-cloth and candlelit setting, ooey gooey homemade pasta dishes. This is the kind of place that makes you feel right at home. Try the lasagnetta, a rolled/pinwheel lasagna creation. It'll change your life.

Il Borgo is one of my all time favorite places in San Francisco. It has a really nice, intimate, neighborhood/local vibe and the food is amazing. The owners are an Italian family who are always so incredibly nice and extremely hospitable. Everything is made fresh everyday, including the pasta. And boy can you tell!  Highly recommend.

Sept 2014 - Cosy, authentic and great Italian place! You feel like you're in a small town in Italy with its furnishing style. We ordered a pasta, a pizza, two desserts to share between three of us - photo attached. Such a satisfying meal!

Without a doubt some of the most authentic Italian food I've had in SF. No need to go to North Beach when you can find delicious homemade pasta and classic sauces in Hayes Valley. Prices are moderate and you'll certainly feel like you're in the middle of Florence.

Great atmosphere, good food, and good service. Its a nice little spot for dinner.

Intimate setting, delicious food, and friendly service.  Enjoyed the homemade pastas (fettuccine and fusilli) and well-balanced sauces. Service was friendly and accommodating.  Make sure to grab an espresso and tiramisu before you head out.
